<br>
Recently, I've attended a few raids with a high end guild on my server, and had the following thoughts.<br>
<br>
Mages want to do damage on raids.. and our pet = a huge chunk of our damage capabilities.<br>
<br>
Each of our pets other than epic, is Immune to something. (Fire/Fire, Earth/Disease, Water/Poision, air/cold)<br>
<br>
Why doesnt the epic have all those immunities?<br>
<br>
I know it's been brought up before, but sheesh, having to have a pet up on one fight that was Immune to Cold, reclaim, Fire next, reclaim...etc etc etc.. isnt the way to go about it, espically in ToV etc...<br>
<br>
Why should I have to put away my new toy to kill Lord Rak'Ashirr in CoM? /boggle <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=182186><img src=http://www.lvcm.com/games/pictures/kelebeksig1.jpg></a> <br>
